title: Earth Aware Toastmasters
body:
At Earth Aware Toastmasters, we practice the art of communication, leadership and public speaking in a learn-by-doing environment that allows us to achieve our goals at our own pace and in a supportive atmosphere. Our members and guests come together to make our meetings fun, welcoming and memorable for all, as we share stories of the Earth, its people and our human experiences.

Want to attend? Shoot us an email at earthaware.toastmasters@gmail.com

title: Hybrid Meeting - Cloverleaf Toastmasters
body:
HYBRID MEETINGS NOW, visit in-person (go to BC Alliance for Arts + Culture, 938 Howe St #100, V6Z 1N9) or online.

Come join us for a lunch break of learning, entertainment and fun! Whatever your level of public speaking, we will help you to quickly develop self-confidence and build personal growth and leadership. Our club has been the proud recipient of the President Distinguished Club Award (the highest Toastmasters award) for 8 years in-a-row. We will be very happy to welcome you as a guest on Wednesday!

When: Every Wednesday from 12:10pm to 1:30pm
Where: Zoom Online Meeting at https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83693020084
Please phone or message 604-617-1498 to let us know that you will be coming, and to get the Zoom password. You can also sign up for our meeting to receive the full details at http://eepurl.com/hko7ej

Cloverleaf Toastmasters Introduction Video: https://youtu.be/CmBkc-NVDF8
For a preview of what Toastmasters meetings are: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=383gehepo8M

**Make sure you join in at least FIVE minutes earlier to deal with any technology issues. We look forward to seeing you online!


Follow us:
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/cloverleafttm
